  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Process Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Act as a technical liaison between Korea HQ and the local site by receiving ongoing technical updates, disseminating them to local employees, and requesting technical support or guidance when required.</li><li>Develop, maintain, and update Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs), including new product qualification,      equipment qualification and operation, and failure analysis.</li><li>Investigate and respond promptly to unexpected production issues such as process deviations and handling      problems.</li><li>Manage and optimize cleaning and coating processes at the production site.</li><li>Communicate effectively with customers and the sales team regarding engineering and process-related issues.</li><li>Follow up on production issues, corrective actions, and customer or internal requests.</li><li>Train and mentor new engineering employees.</li><li>Update and maintain MES data for existing and new parts.</li><li>Measure parts and prepare relevant technical and inspection documentation.</li><li>Liaise with suppliers and vendors to support process and material requirements.</li><li>Support Quality Assurance (QA) activities, including internal and external audits.</li><li>Perform other ad-hoc tasks as assigned by the supervisor.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree or higher in Materials Science, Engineering, or a related field.</li><li>Minimum of 5 years of experience in the semiconductor industry. <br />Preferred: Hands-on experience in cleaning and/or coating processes within the semiconductor industry.</li><li>Strong knowledge of chemical materials and related processes.</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office applications (Excel, Word, PowerPoint).</li><li>Good written and verbal communication skills in English are required for effective communication with customers and cross-functional teams.</li><li>Ability to communicate in Korean is required for collaboration with the Korea HQ engineering team on technical and operational matters.</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
